    <text id="B0204T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell's letter describes the articles of clothing being shipped to Waldo for
                    distribution. McDonnell explains to Waldo how he should account for and
                    distribute the clothing.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/>Head <abbr expan="Quarters">Qrs</abbr>. 9<hi rend="super">t</hi>
                    Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A.
                        Comr</abbr><lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-12-14"><abbr expan="December">Dec</abbr> 14<hi rend="super">t</hi><abbr expan="1868">/68</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your letter announcing the receipt of a supply of clothing has been received.</p>

                <p>The articles were Invoiced to me and receipted for on the 25th of last month.
                        <abbr expan="Although">Altho'</abbr> I requested their shipment to you.
                        <abbr expan="Major">Maj.</abbr> White failed to inform me to whom they were
                    sent, or I should have advised you of their shipment. The following are the
                    articles Invoiced <abbr expan="Major">Maj.</abbr></p>

                <p>Trousers, <abbr expan="pair">pr.</abbr> 30 - <unclear>Osuaburg</unclear>
                    <abbr expan="yards">yds</abbr> 120 - Blankets Woolen 20 - Brogans, <abbr
                        expan="pairs">prs</abbr> 40 - Dress Coats 15 - Over Coats 15 - Mens shoes
                        <abbr expan="pairs">prs</abbr> 40 - Dresses 40 - Chemises 40.</p>

                <p>The Dress Coats and Over Coats being <unclear>GM</unclear>
                    <unclear>Shoes</unclear> are to be issued on separate rolls.</p>

                <p>I shall send by this mail a sufficient number of Receipt Rolls. Please describe
                    the articles exactly as above, making the "Osuaburg Trousers" <pb n="2"/>you
                    already had, a separate item from the "Trousers" just received, as they are
                    accounted for as per Invoice.</p>

                <p><abbr expan="Major">Maj.</abbr> White desires that all this clothing be accounted
                    for on receipt rolls, and if not all issued, the balance be turned over to the
                    School Teachers for issue.</p>

                <p>Please return Receipt Rolls accounting for all this clothing as early as the 25th
                    inst.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">Svt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">Sub Asst
                            Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
